Reasoning: The paper deals with the analysis of social media data, specifically Twitter, to study the origins and pathways of trends, how they compete for popularity at the local level to emerge as winners at the country level, and what dynamics underlie their production and consumption in different geographic areas. This falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Social and Information Retrieval (cs.SD), Social and Economic Networks (cs.SOC), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), and Computation and Language (cs.CL).
